She didn't want to go. So I go to the church. And I had never heard Dr. King speak before. Never heard him. I mean, they pay attention to him.

01:58:41.000 --> 01:59:01.000
I was one third from the front of the full pit. And he gets up. He says, ladies and gentlemen, brothers and sisters, the text of my sermon today, as a role and responsibility of the Negro professional in aiding our less fortunate brothers and sisters, struggling to beat him in the South. So I said, one smart dude.

01:59:01.000 --> 01:59:20.000
Then he begins to speak. And he begins to describe what he's doing much more in detail and texturing. I had never heard or seen him speak before.

01:59:20.000 --> 01:59:46.000
More accurately, I had never heard another human being walking on two legs on this earth speak that way before. It was mesmerizing. It was like, you know, you could hear a pin drop. And he was, you know, as he was so intense.

01:59:46.000 --> 01:59:59.000
And he was so serious. And then he pauses during the course of the sermon. And he says, for example, there's a young man sitting in his church today.

02:00:00.000 --> 02:00:12.000
My friends in New York, who are lawyers for whom I have great respect. My friends in New York tell me that this young man's brain has been touched by Jesus.

02:00:14.000 --> 02:00:25.000
They tell me that when this young man, a lawyer does any legal research, he goes all the way back to the time of 1066.

