02:01:58.000 --> 02:02:12.000
And the lyrics in that poem talk about washable and domestic. She's washing the stairs. She pauses on the landing. She says, I'm doing this for you son. Don't you, don't you give up.

02:02:13.000 --> 02:02:25.000
Life ain't been no crystal stair. Don't you give up. Dr. King changes the lyrics and puts my mother as the actor in the poem instead of the washable.

02:02:25.000 --> 02:02:40.000
At which point I began to cry because I get disturbed by, you know, I knew that she had begun the greatest pain I've experienced in my life. And then I began to recognize how much.

02:02:41.000 --> 02:02:58.000
She loved me. How much she has sacrificed. She didn't see any. She didn't see any other things. She didn't see me graduate from college. She didn't see me graduate from law school. She didn't see me have anything. She was a great teacher.

